This paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with computational trust mechanisms and their application in trust and reputation models. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as trust assessment is a crucial aspect of security. Additionally, the paper involves empirical studies, which may place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with fusion and discount operators, which may also place it in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
